John Goodwin, 75, shot himself outside of Rockingham County Superior Courthouse in New Hampshire on Friday morning . 
  Goodwin was on trial this week on six counts of aggravated felonious sexual assault . 
  Prosecutors say Goodwin repeatedly sexually assaulted an underage student . 
  He was airlifted to a hospital with life-threatening injuries . 
  The jury was deliberating when Goodwin shot himself . 
 